events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored a season-high 41 points, and the New York Knicks overcame 42 from Victor Wembanyama in a monster Christmas debut to edge the San Antonio Spurs 117-114 on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges scores season-high 41, Knicks withstand Wembanyama's monster Christmas debut to edge Spurs

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 26 points, and the Minnesota Timberwolves held on for a 105-99 Christmas Day victory over Dallas after Mavericks superstar Luka Doncic left the game with a strained left calf.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 26, Wolves hold on to beat Mavs 105-99 after Doncic injury

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid popped up from a pregame fall and scored 27 points with nine rebounds, making 4 of 5 from 3-point range and sinking a pair of free throws with 3 seconds left to turn back Boston’s final rally and lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 118-114...
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid shakes off pregame fall, leads Sixers to 118-114 win over Celtics

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Austin Reaves scored the winning layup with one second left after Stephen Curry tied it on a 31-foot 3-pointer with seven seconds remaining, LeBron James had 31 points and 10 assists playing in his NBA-record 19th Christmas Day game, and the Los...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 31 in record 19th Christmas Day game as Lakers hold off Curry, Warriors 115-113

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant and Bradley Beal each scored 27 points and the Phoenix Suns beat the Denver Nuggets 110-100 on Wednesday night in the nightcap to the NBA’s Christmas slate of games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant and Beal score 27 points each, Suns beat Nuggets 110-100 to close out Christmas slate
